multiflexi-executor (1.16.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * executor -r now queues the RunTemplate job for "now" and waits for the
    daemon to run it, then reproduces the job's stdout, stderr and exit code
    (instead of running the job inline). The daemon must be running.
  * Add -t/--timeout option and RUNTEMPLATE_WAIT_TIMEOUT (default 300s, 0 =
    wait forever); exit 124 when the daemon does not finish the job in time.
  * Add RUNTEMPLATE_WAIT_POLL to tune the completion poll interval.
  * Add tests/run-template-wait.sh integration test for both paths.
  * Add man pages: multiflexi-executor(8) and multiflexi-run-template(1)

 -- vitex <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Wed, 04 Jun 2026 08:00:00 +0200

